The EFK (Elasticsearch, Fluentd, Kibana) also known as logging pipeline.

[Elasticsearch]
It search engine using distributed data storage to index and store the logging data heap from each node.
Its primary work is to store logs and retrive logs from Fluentd.

[Fluentd]
It collect and aggregate all the logging data on each  node and ships that into Elasticsearch.

[Kibana]
It provide a dashboard for Elasticsearch for visualization and analysis.

[Workflow]
Fluentd (Server/Containerization - Logs) ----> Elasticsearch ----> Kibana
